    "excerpt": "A world has arrived where mistakes are not allowed. In order to get a job, there must be no gaps in your life, and if there are gaps, you must be able to explain them perfectly. While praising those who...",
    "body_en": "<p style=\"text-align: justify; \">A world that does not allow mistakes has arrived. In order to get a job, there must be no gaps in your life, and if there are gaps, you must be able to explain them perfectly.</p> <p style=\"text-align: justify; \">While we praise those who ran toward only one goal, those who have come a long way deserve to be praised, but they are not as good as those who ran forward. As to how the world came to be like this, it is definitely because of the world's technologies that are moving towards perfection.</p> <p>19 different routes to get from home to work, with an interval of 0.001 seconds that you probably don't need to know. We mobilize all kinds of technologies to achieve the optimal efficiency we need. From pop-up notifications that there will soon be empty seats in the next subway car to unvisited travel destinations that people with similar tastes as me are dissatisfied with, we live in a world that does not allow for errors.</p> <p>In such a perfect world, sufficiently perfect AI is learning and developing the world at an unprecedented rate. Now, maybe I'm the only one who isn't perfect.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"20230901000639_dtwtozvz.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2309/20230901192926_nhmznrlk.jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height:557px;\"/></p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><br/></p> <p>?쏱erfect?? is there a word that brings such satisfaction and displeasure at the same time? A ?쁯erfectionist??needs to fix his behavior, and a ?쁯erfect person??needs to have humanity. Even on popular dating shows, couples who are perfectly matched from the beginning are not popular.</p> <p>At one time, a video comparing smart speakers from each manufacturer surfaced through an algorithm. At that time, what caught people's attention was Company K, which made the most mistakes. Although the success rate of the command is low, about 1,000 people liked the comment saying they wanted to buy it because it was so funny.</p> <p>So, this thought suddenly occurred to me. If we make it known that human resources are an essential element in creating AI, will people become less fearful? Or will I feel anxious even if I use AI well?</p> <p>First of all, without data centers built by people, we would have no algorithms. There is a good reason why Open AI, the maker of GPT, joined hands with MS. Unable to cover operating costs, GPT continues to release paid versions, and Microsoft is expanding its vertical business. The maintenance cost amounts to approximately 925 million won per day. How dare Microsoft sign a contract with a nuclear fusion company? From the moment rent is overdue, GPT cannot even be turned on.</p> <p>Next, Human In The Loop (HITL) refers to a task in which a person intervenes to correct or supplement tasks such as automated systems, such as deep learning. Numerous studies unanimously say that having humans manually process data for AI to learn helps achieve better performance. Many companies still need developers to create AI, and big data departments that were thought to disappear are still overflowing with new students.</p> <p>In addition, it is very famous that in the 1990s, Gary Kasparov, the world chess champion, lost the championship to an AI called ?쁃eep Blue?? but then formed a joint team with the AI and ultimately defeated the AI.(The opposing AI could not move the chess pieces on its own, so it had to get help from humans!) Afterwards, the AI ?뗢땧as defeated by the joint team in events such as baduk, quizzes, and poker.</p> <p>Even people need help. This is especially natural for machines created by humans. Needs human help. However, the point that needs to be made is that we are not saying that we should be reassured that AI is under our feet. Recently, generative AI not only understands the intent of the first search term entered by a person and predicts the next search term, but also infers why this search term was needed.</p> <p>But I want to shout out that even this cannot be perfect on its own. AI companies such as Naver's HyperCLOVAThis is because AI, which absorbs information without heuristics, is not only difficult to control, but also requires human feedback and continuous improvement work (with people attached).</p> <p>We are like sailors at the wheel of a ship. Or it could be like walking your dog. When Sarang tries to leave the designated trail and enter the grass, gently pull on his leash with his fingertips and lead him back to a safe path. When Sarang tries to run towards the child, hold the leash briefly and walk away from the child.</p> <p>The world looks perfect when seen from afar, but when you look closely, everything is tangled up here and there. Just as people live together in many countries on the African continent with straight borders and in Manhattan with straight roads running through the city, the chat pages we access such as ChatGPT and Bard are very clean and modern, making them seem like modern products in themselves, but they are the product of countless people working overtime.</p> <p>Even if I have lived a life full of mistakes, just as I want the person I like to only see the beauty in my actions, IT workers also want the AI they created with their hands to look perfect. We live in a world where mistakes are not tolerated, but where many people have learned how to hide their mistakes.</p> <p>Even if they live for 60 or 80 years, let?셲 look at adults who say things like ?쏧?셶e never seen such a strange person in my life.?쒷o matter how long I live, a perfect world will never come.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"_80efcede-1c03-42b2-97ec-20916e8b6cca.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2309/20230901002724_mboaxkqu.jpg\" style=\"width:660px;height: 660px;\"/></p>",
