    "title_ko": "AI, ?대뼸寃?洹밸났?좉퉴?",
    "title_en": "AI, how do we overcome it?",
    "excerpt": "This article is about AI, why is it so difficult?This article continues from . Previously, I tried to infer from psychological principles why AI was difficult and difficult to step into. In par...",
    "body_en": "<p style=\"text-align: justify; \"> <i>This article is a continuation of <a href=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/news/view.php?no=65427\" target=\"_blank\"><b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">AI, why is it so difficult?</span></b></a></i> </p> <p>Until now, I had inferred why AI was difficult and difficult to step into using psychological principles. In particular, AI is now creating a life that never existed before, and many people are quickly adapting to it. Moreover, there are a lot of technologies that people are not aware of! (Are you also... AI?) Most personalized product recommendations are based on AI technology, and the same goes for Apple's Face ID. AI is already ubiquitous in everyday life, but it just doesn?셳 have the word ?쁀I??on its forehead.</p> <p>Now, the term <b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">ambient computing</span></b> is being used. In other words, it is ?쐔echnology like air.?쒿he field of IoT is developing most prosperously, with the light in the living room turning on automatically when you enter the house without you being conscious of it, and the temperature and humidity in the air conditioner being adjusted accordingly.</p> <p>In addition, blockchain is emerging along with the rapid development of AI. Sam Altman of Open AI, who developed ChatGPT, is traveling around the world promoting the blockchain <b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">World Coin Project</span></b> that he is working on. Simply put, in a world where it is difficult to distinguish between machines and humans, current identification methods will become useless, so a new financial system is needed.</p> <p>As the number of bank counters has decreased, online banking has become essential, and it is not long before we need to manage crypto (cryptocurrency market and assets) using blockchain technology. All of this can be seen as a ripple effect of AI. Now, just like during the Industrial Revolution, there is no other solution. I have no choice but to adapt.</p> <div class=\"cheditor-caption-wrapper\" style=\"text-align: center;\"> <figure class=\"cheditor-caption\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background-color: #d97706; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 660px;\"> <img alt=\"OIG.kNnyWz.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2307/20230704160530_zofpgnqh.jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 660px;\"/> <figcaption class=\"cheditor-caption-text\" style=\"margin: 6px 10px 6px 10px; text-align: left; line-height: 18px; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.04em; text-align:justify;\">Image created using Bing AI</figcaption> </figure> </div> <p>Then, is there any way for our society to respond?</p> <p> <b><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1) Formation of social discourse - </span></b>Last March, due to the shock that ChatGPT gave to the world, celebrities including Yuval Harari and Elon Musk called for a temporary halt in development in consideration of the impact of large AI on society. Since it is a generative AI that is difficult for even developers to control, the position was that social confusion could be reduced only if development continued after social regulations were established. </p> <p>However, this letter only has social meaning and has no real effect. Since then, numerous companies, including Microsoft's BingChat and Google's Bard, are competing to dominate the market. For commercial reasons, it seems impossible to control the pace of technological advancement.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>In that case, there is no choice but for experts such as sociologists and legal scholars to come up with appropriate regulations as soon as possible. Additionally, we must have a sense of ownership to tame the wild horse called AI rather than being one step behind in fear. If the AI encounters a problem or causes discomfort, please do not hesitate to contact the company directly or form a social discourse in the community.</p> <p> <b><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2) Responsibility that must be placed on companies that brought technology into existence - </span></b>Microsoft Vice President Brad Smith said in his book &lt;Book of Technology&gt;Accordingly, Microsoft is carrying out various activities to prevent technological alienation. In Korea, this is equivalent to operating an AI school with the Ministry of Employment and Labor or participating in a youth work-experience support project. Companies that offer technology like this should be required to provide education accordingly. </p> <p>In addition, social responsibilities are required, as prompted by the open letter. Companies should initially establish an inspection team to thoroughly remove elements that may be harmful to users before launch, such as copyright issues for AI-generated creations, which have already been deeply controversial, and legal liability issues when chat-type AI makes comments that attack users. As it becomes more difficult for the country and the company itself to control, the number of affected users will inevitably increase.</p> <p>Furthermore, a firewall must be erected to prevent people using AI in ways that countries and companies cannot imagine. Just as you can make a real gun with a 3D printer, AI that continues to learn will have an even greater impact.</p> <div class=\"cheditor-caption-wrapper\" style=\"text-align: center;\"> <figure class=\"cheditor-caption\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background-color: #d97706; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 660px;\"> <img alt=\"OIG. GWtqW1ReD414WPo.tZ.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2307/20230704160930_ukwgsrww.jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 660px;\"/> <figcaption class=\"cheditor-caption-text\" style=\"margin: 6px 10px 6px 10px; text-align: left; line-height: 18px; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.04em; text-align:justify;\">Image created using Bing AI</figcaption> </figure> </div> <p>The saying that those who know how to use AI will survive has become so familiar to the point of clich챕. All companies are calling for digital transformation to avoid repeating the precedent that followed during the Industrial Revolution, when factories that stubbornly refused to introduce machines went bankrupt. It is a huge social trend that companies naturally have no choice but to adopt AI, and consumers have no choice but to be influenced by.</p> <p>However, let us remember that the reins of AI are in the hands of humans, and that only by joining hands can we overcome the great mountain.</p> ",
