    "body_en": "<p style=\"text-align: justify; \">Bill Gates recently attended ?쁀rtificial Intelligence Forward 2023??and said that when AI assistants begin to be completely overhauled, existing search sites will disappear. Sejong City?셲 self-driving transportation vehicle ?쁓hucle?? which incorporates AI technology, is It replaces public buses by operating on the optimal route while carrying a large number of passengers who board at the desired location. Virtual human Beyond developing and creating advertisements, we have signed contracts with companies so that celebrities can transform their appearances into AI and use it. By concluding this, we are changing the paradigm of marketing.</p> <p>The point where AI came into our lives was probably the robot vacuum cleaner or YouTube algorithm. I'm used to it It seems like enough time has passed, but AI-related news is new enough to fill newspaper pages every day. The term ?쁀I??has become tiresomely familiar, but why is it still Is it new and difficult?<b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">First of all, AI has several difficult There are several reasons.</span></b></p> <div class=\"cheditor-caption-wrapper\" style=\"text-align: center;\"> <figure class=\"cheditor-caption\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background-color: #d97706; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 660px;\"><img alt=\"587bccad-c16b-4c2d-b684-90f988648568.png\"src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2306/20230622182718_nussbfxm.png\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 660px;\"/> <figcaption class=\"cheditor-caption-text\" style=\"margin: 6px 10px 6px 10px; text-align: left; line-height: 18px; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.04em; text-align:justify;\">Image created using Bing AI</figcaption> </figure> </div> <p class=\"article-subheading\"><b>1) Resistance to change to change)</b></p> <p><b> </b></p> <p>Even when there was no AI, we lived without much inconvenience. For a long time we It can be seen that the analog lifestyle has become an unconscious habit. Everyone knows that habits are difficult to change. However, AI suddenly appeared, and even the smallest actions, from writing emails to automatically ordering detergent, from online tasks to offline tasks, were all taken care of. They are knocking on the door to change everything.</p> <p>Early adopters, who account for 15% of all consumers, gladly welcome this innovative change. I swear They probably haven't turned the light switch on or off by hand for at least five years. Now, a house like a smart apartment that can be completely controlled with a home IoT app. You may wish for it or may already own it. However, most people have a homeostasis that wants to stick to their existing way of living. Therefore, it is natural to show resistance to change.</p> <p class=\"article-subheading\"><b>2) Fatigue due to pressure from new technologies</b></p> <p>Among the resistance, new technologies and There is ?쁳echnical resistance?? which refers to the attitude and reluctance of people to accept a method. The way I used to live Even if you don't want to change, everyone is changing except you, so if you don't know AI, life is unsustainable.</p> <p>Digital literacy is lagging behind. Just as people ended up not being able to order at McDonald's, maladaptation to AI can be caused by job changes or It will not only change the way we work, but also affect our overall lives. The work style and speed of all occupations, including designers, developers, accountants, and planners, are Aside from the fact that AI utilization ability has begun to be included in work skills, the immediate The pressure to make a living has begun.</p> <p>Not only existing companies but also startups Naturally, AI is being used. According to Gartner, among AI, generative AI such as GPT The amount invested over the past three years has exceeded 2 trillion won. This also means that AI will be everywhere around consumers. The AI revolution has changed the landscape and all companies are pursuing digitalization, so consumers From my perspective, the number of things has become too many. They say it takes a million hours to change a single habit, but dozens, hundreds, Changing thousands of habits is bound to be a daunting task. This is both resistance and fatigue.</p> <p class=\"article-subheading\"><b>3) Axiom of choice and Hick?셲 Law</b></p> <p>But how can I keep up? Mr. A searches for ChatGPT on Google and connects to Open AI, then immediately closes the window. I don't know what to search for, and there aren't any popular posts, so this AI and I are left alone on a remote island with nowhere to go.</p> <p>What if you have a wide range of choices? It becomes difficult to decide what to input, which can ultimately lead to confusion (Axiom of Choice). Also, if too many choices are given, it may take a long time to make the final choice. and the burden of having to think increases (Hicks' law).we are I didn't think too much when searching on Naver or Google. If you were curious about the recipe for seaweed soup, all you had to do was enter ?쁲eaweed soup??</p> <p>a) ?쁓eaweed Soup Recipe??I don't think ChatGPT was created to search for things like that. <b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">Isn't it used in slightly grander situations?</span></b></p> <p>b) <b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">The words get longer.</span></b> ?쏷ell me how to make seaweed soup!?쓂hy can?셳 I just put in a keyword? It?셲 a chat after all.</p> <p>c) <b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">There are too many posts.</span></b> Number 1, 2, 3?쪰t lists the order, but I don't even click on the posts with 'suppressionism' attached, so I can't believe I read all of them! Youtube or If I had chosen the blog, I could have seen the amount of water or the strength of the ladle stirring the pot through photos and videos without reading the article!</p> <p>d) <b><span style=\"color: #d97706;\">Just do what you are told.</span></b>If you search again on YouTube or blogs, you will find ingredients, substitute ingredients, and leftovers. It also provides useful tips such as how to process ingredients.(We all get serendipity online, whether we are aware of it or not. Expect knowledge)</p> <p>So, Microsoft's Bing gives many options on the first page, and when one chat is completed, It does provide examples of tail questions. However, it still takes effort to enter search terms, and the results feel somewhat less rich than the existing search environment.</p> <p>There are countless more reasons than this. It will be blocking the road to becoming an AI user. Next In the article, opinions are expressed on ?쏶o what should we do???Present.</p> ",
