    "body_en": "<p style=\"text-align: justify; \">Not long ago, while working, I took an empty water cup. I headed to the water purifier. When I looked down at my hand as the wetness ran down my fingers, I saw that there was not a cup but a desk mirror. As this is becoming more frequent, it is natural to look back on your family history. But older adults He lived a very healthy old age, with black and abundant hair that was passed down from generation to generation. Something very strange is happening to me, who was born into a lucky family that is far from the disease called ?쁡ementia.??/p> <p>I am not the only one experiencing this. As the new term Youngzheimer (young + Alzheimer) shows, Memory problems among the younger generation are not an individual phenomenon.40% of the 2030 generation Lee Sang diagnosed himself as Youngzheimer. Excessive smartphone use affects memory It's been a long time since negative news came out, especially when using a smartphone while watching TV. If you engage in multitasking, it is fatal to the decline in memory function.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"2025_20200703174623600.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2107/20210701001757_xdqbswod.jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height:692px;\"/></p> <p>However, if you simply leave a note or someone else's contact information, This is not just because the smartphone remembers it for us. This is because the necessary brain functions have also changed as the digital environment has changed. As the amount of information increases, it becomes necessary to make decisions in a short period of time, and the brain I have adapted to this environment.</p> <p>For example, traditional reading is the language of the brain, If the visual processing area is fused and focuses on remembering the content of information, Knowledge acquisition uses the prefrontal cortex, which is directly connected to problem-solving or decision-making areas, such as which keyword to enter and whether to click on a hyperlink in the wiki dictionary or not.</p> <p>An analog method of memorizing a friend's phone number. Even if you choose to do so, it is very difficult to maintain the existing way of using your brain because the surrounding environment has changed. This is not a problem that can be solved simply by telling individuals, ?쏝eware of multitasking!??/p> <p>Therefore, text in print and electronic media There are also increasing views that they cannot be viewed as the same thing. In particular, if a book using existing type has already left the author's hand, Texts, including recent web novels, can be continuously edited. Anyone can edit As the number of Wikipedia-type web pages increases, changes in digital text continue to occur, and openness has become a main characteristic.</p> <p>When you search the web, you may find something different from your initial search term. There are times when you find the mouse cursor standing 20km away. Rather than my fault for not being able to concentrate, I should see it as a characteristic of digital text. Countless hyperlinks It is a process of acquiring selective knowledge rather than the purpose of reading the context in a paragraph. Moreover, each link has an order Because it is not a thing, there is virtually no such thing as context.</p> <p>In addition, only a very small portion of the key information needed by an individual is found on one page, and it depends on the individual's diversity and purpose. Accordingly, the same phrase is connected to another hyperlink, so each user has no choice but to accept it differently. In the end, one Tossi It is natural that the difference between a person who has access to a correct electronic document and a person who has access to the same content in a printed version becomes even larger.</p> <p>Traditional reading where the overall context of the book is important Because web-based knowledge acquisition that follows the flow is viewed by the same standards, digital texts are undervalued and seen as a problem. I'm pinched. The world is changing, but people are asked to maintain homeostasis. I don't know how much of a leap in logic this is.</p> <p>Rather, Hayles, As suggested by N. K., we can improve digital literacy and enable reader-controlled hyperreading (hyperreading). should be aimed at being able to read. There is no way to reduce smartphone usage. It's an era without one. Too much is already being done online, and the cloud More and more things are being moved to web-based, including.</p> <p>Digital detox is the idea of gradually eliminating the digital environment. It is also true that it is emerging as an important issue. However, AI is also rapidly Can we stay away from digital now that it is developing? Shouldn?셳 this be solved within digital? If you can't control the flow, you have to jump on the wave and learn how to surf.</p> <p>Multitasking is ruining my memory now. Because of this, it is realistically difficult to stop multitasking right away. It's hard to say that it's a huge motivator. Some say that digital media change the experience of time itself. Spatio-temporal flow The point is that it does not flow only in the direction we know. It's not that our memory is broken, but that we're building a new system. It may be that we have not yet figured out the system.</p> <p>The digital environment is still unfamiliar to humans. Contrary to what we felt, it hadn't been long since it approached us. As an unconditional disease Rather than naming it, it may be more correct to redefine the memory circuit that the younger generation has.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"3554274142_LOYItRgp_the_memory_center.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2107/20210701212348_xhuppyug.jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height:438px;\"/></p> <p class=\"article-reference\">Source</p>\n<p class=\"article-reference\">Hyung Lee, Sooyoung Nam, Chung Eui-jin, Seung-gi Cha, Gyeong-ryul Lee, Ae-ryeong Kim, So-ryun Kim, Gyeong-hwan Park, So-young Kim, Woo Hee-hee (2019). Text technology mobility. Alfie.</p>",
