    "title_ko": "諛붾땲, 諛붾땲, ?밴렐, ?밴렐, ?몃줈???以꾩뿬二쇰뒗 ?뚮━",
    "title_en": "Barney, Barney, carrot, carrot, a sound that reduces loneliness",
    "excerpt": "I have a friend who particularly hates carrots in curry. My dog ?뗢땊oes not eat carrots unless they are domestically grown carrots. And ?쁂arrot Market?? a mobile-based second-hand trading platform, does ...",
    "body_en": "<p style=\"text-align: justify; \">I have a friend who particularly dislikes carrots in curry. My dog ?뗢땊oes not eat carrots unless they are domestically grown carrots. And ?쁂arrot Market?? a mobile-based second-hand trading platform, does not allow trading unless it is near you.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>Carrots are not the base of curry!???쁂arrot Market??has become a basic application in August 2020, exceeding 10 million monthly users (Baedal Minjok 13.18 million, YouTube 39.15 million, respectively. Source Nielsen Research, big data platform company IGA Works).</p> <p>As interest in the environment becomes more widespread, everyone has the phrase ?쏡on?셳 buy new!??in the back of their minds, and the value of old items has increased due to the retro craze. As minimalism becomes popular and the number of single-person households continues to increase, it becomes necessary to share items that must be purchased in bulk, such as eggs. Personally, I get tired of information about too many products and try to escape from the fatigue by reducing my options to products that just happen to be used.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>The consumer sentiment index or economic sentiment index, which is an index indicating the perceived economic level, has always hovered around 100. If it falls below 100, it means that each sentiment has contracted compared to the past, and it has never touched the 80 line before 2013. However, the fact that it is hovering around the 50 to 80 range this year could serve as a background for paying attention to relatively inexpensive used products. The trend of the times is supporting the growth of the used market.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>Let?셲 consider the relationship between a rabbit and a carrot. If you look at it closely, carrots are actually hay, not a rabbit's staple food. An interesting fact is that the app classification of Carrot Market is ?쁲ocial networking??rather than ?쁲hopping?? These appearances, which do not correspond to superficial information, also show how people use the object. The connection between rabbits and carrots is because familiar animations have always expressed it that way, and the reason Carrot Market changed the app classification is because users changed the nature of the application.</p> <div class=\"cheditor-caption-wrapper\" style=\"text-align: center;\"> <figure class=\"cheditor-caption\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background-color: #d97706; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 660px;\"> <img alt=\"Carrot Market.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2010/20201030110055_pvarcpgl.jpg\" style=\"width: 660px; height: 336px;\"/> <figcaption class=\"cheditor-caption-text\" style=\"margin: 6px 10px 6px 10px; text-align: left; line-height: 18px; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.04em; text-align:justify;\">Source Carrot Market</figcaption> </figure> </div> <p>The existing mobile used trading market and Carrot Market show different aspects. It also has the function of a human resources office with a 5-minute standby basis, such as selling and selling that can be handled right away with your slippers in tow; during kimchi season, the kimchi made by a big house is overflowing; during fish season, it shares freshly caught seasonal fish; and even offers a reward for catching cockroaches. I started saying hello to the people next door again.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p style=\"text-align: justify; \">In fact, in Carrot Market, 1 out of 10 transactions are counted as repeat transactions with the same person. The more the application is activated, the more people in the neighborhood can gather together. This social nature created a differentiation and led to significant growth compared to classic used trading apps.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p style=\"text-align: center; \">*</p> <div> <br/> </div> <p>One of the places that people who travel to Europe always choose is the flea market formed in each village. It is not a flea market in the narrow sense that sells antiques and handicrafts, but is similar to a 3-day or 5-day market where home-grown agricultural and marine products are also commonly sold. Even bartering occurs.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>I left for a foreign country in the era of globalization, but I got to see the local community. The question is whether the local market, which was established at the opposite point of globalization, which is emphasized in the media, in books, on the employment front, and for the youth and the elderly, is really the opposite point. The question is, can't we have the advantages of both?</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>It's really strange how people become connected through one application. Localization is also taking place in Korea, which pursues global K-( ). As movement between regions became more frequent, the Isa rice cake culture was disappearing, and lonely death was recognized as a problem. As the scope expands from the loneliness of the elderly to the loneliness of the young, it has become impossible to explain the 2000s without using the word disconnection. However, isn't human diversification the reason why nature does not give up on humans easily?</p> <p>Through a second-hand transaction application that encourages direct contact, the sense of belonging of living in the same area is shared with anonymous people, and small conversations such as ?쏻hen can I take the dog for a walk in this Corona situation??? sharing a good cafe for studying alone, or ?쏧 like the new vegan restaurant??have emerged. We are discovering ways to solve ?쁲olitude?? From second-hand transactions that expanded into Korean-style flea markets and village gatherings.</p> <div class=\"cheditor-caption-wrapper\" style=\"text-align: center;\"> <figure class=\"cheditor-caption\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); background-color: #d97706; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 640px;\"> <img alt=\"slowfood.jpg\" src=\"https://www.artinsight.co.kr/data/tmp/2010/20201030110232_oavhhcfs.jpg\" style=\"width: 640px; height: 427px;\"/> <figcaption class=\"cheditor-caption-text\" style=\"margin: 6px 10px; line-height: 18px; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.04em; text-align: justify;\">slowfood</figcaption> </figure> </div> <p>One of the reasons I enjoyed the Bunny Bunny game was that there was no need for names or nicknames to refer to people. Just watch the people to your left and right. When meeting someone for the first time, just one piece of information can be more of a guarantee than you think. Tongseongmyeong somehow seems to have the futility and risk of a one-time meeting.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>Instead, it is given that the person's workplace or residence is near this meeting place. If the other person's name is all I have, what kind of conversation can I have with people who only meet once? It is a coincidence or necessity that ?쁱egion??was chosen with minimal information. Your ?쁲olitude??may be reduced just by being in contact with people who live right next to you.</p> <p> <br/> </p> <p>I google it, Google is like that. The verb ?쁆oogle??is used more frequently than serach, which means ?쁲earch.?셒hile waiting for a friend near the subway station, you may have been asked the question, ?쏡o you have any carrots???쓄ou may have heard ?쏞arrot!??ringing on the phone of someone sitting at the table next to you at a restaurant. I think we are now in the process of creating warmth around you with the word ?쁟arrot.??/p>",
